      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty specific way to define it though. u say it has to be \"grounded in social justice\" to be good. isn't that basically saying that nationalism is only okay if it follows a specific progressive agenda? it feels like u're setting up a standard where nationalism is only valid if it looks a certain way, which seems a bit biased. shouldn't a nation's identity just be about its own people and traditions regardless of those specific political frameworks?",
